    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Vegetable Cutlets are crispy patties made with mashed veggies and spices, shallow fried to golden perfection. A perfect evening snack or starter.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>25 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>2 boiled potatoes</li>
        <li>1/2 cup chopped mixed vegetables (carrot, beans, peas)</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp garam masala</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp cumin powder</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>2 tbsp breadcrumbs</li>
        <li>1 green chili (finely chopped)</li>
        <li>Chopped coriander leaves</li>
        <li>Oil for shallow frying</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Boil and mash all vegetables. Mix in spices, salt, breadcrumbs, and coriander.</li>
        <li>Shape into round cutlets.</li>
        <li>Heat oil in a pan and shallow fry both sides until golden brown.</li>
        <li>Serve hot with mint chutney or ketchup.</li>
    </ol>
